race.comment: DELA BELLA (1) has settled back both starts this preparation and finished them off well enough. She's suited stepping up to the mile and she's capable of sitting handier. This looks a nice race for her. FEDORA (7) presented second-up and was beaten less than 2L at Ballarat, stepping up to this trip. She won't have to improve much to be a winning chance. MISLIGHT (4) raced well in town over this distance before the break and second-up can show more like that form. RED FEATHERS (5) resumed at Sale but was cruelled by a wide gate. The market said she'd need it anyway. She is back after 7 days and showed enough early doors to consider with the extra fitness. REEL CRYSTAL (8) maps well and was tracking well before the latest. Finally draws a low gate and the drop back to the mile should suit better.
